"{\"uid\": \"sbs.com.au-news-article-your-guide-to-the-2024-paris-olympics-bp43a34q7\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Stream free online, anytime  Discover your world of SBS  Sign in or create an account  or  Stream free online, anytime  Get in touch:  Highlights around SBS:  Follow Us:  SBS acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of Country and their connections and continuous care for the skies, lands and waterways throughout Australia.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony for the 2024 Paris Olympics will be held on Friday, 26 July.Source:Getty/Kevin Voigt  New national sporting heroes are about to emerge and already adored athletes could cement their place in history at the 2024 Olympic Games in Paris, France.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 582, \"end\": 588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9957430568241925, \"rank\": 0.002317517658535885, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be the 30th Summer Olympic Games featuring an Australian contingent and much of the nation is about to turn its focus to the athletes in green and gold.\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 647, \"end\": 657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9995366421015613, \"rank\": 0.0004635569299922922, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some events, including football, rugby sevens, handball, and archery have alreadykicked off before the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So what's in store for this year's Games?\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The city of Paris will be on display as part of the opening ceremony for this year's Olympics.\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 1014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time in history, the ceremony will not be held in a stadium.\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, boats will ferry countries' teams along theRiver Seine, through the heart of Paris.\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1150, \"end\": 1155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.9891169211989266e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1178, \"end\": 1183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators are expected to line a six-kilometre section of the banks of the Seine to watch the proceedings.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1262, \"end\": 1267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.9891169211989266e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The parade will end near the Eiffel Tower at the Trocad\\u00e9ro, the marble esplanade where official proceedings and performances will take place.\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1344, \"end\": 1353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"score\": 0.9730907954876998, \"rank\": 0.023351147168026228, \"text\": \"Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the parade will begin at about 7.30pm on Friday 26 July (local time) in Paris,those in Australia will have to be up early on the morning of Saturday 27 July if they want to watch it live.\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1516, \"end\": 1521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1531, \"end\": 1540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will start at3.30am AESTfor viewers in Victoria, NSW, Queensland, Tasmania, and the ACT,3am ACSTfor those in the Northern Territory and South Australia, and1.30am AWSTfor Western Australians.\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1675, \"end\": 1683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_Australian_rules_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9958360549715867, \"rank\": 0.004181125740816315, \"text\": \"Victoria\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_Australian_rules_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_Australian_rules_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales\", \"score\": 0.9999507686643486, \"rank\": 4.347734974318358e-05, \"text\": \"NSW\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_South_Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 1690, \"end\": 1700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queensland\", \"score\": 0.9964721400700268, \"rank\": 0.0035385567109315723, \"text\": \"Queensland\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queensland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queensland\"}, {\"begin\": 1702, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tasmania\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.907838348876668e-12, \"text\": \"Tasmania\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tasmania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tasmania\"}, {\"begin\": 1807, \"end\": 1814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9999878232092808, \"rank\": 7.158620921744847e-06, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"B-Boys and B-Girls will face off in France as breakdancing, or breaking, features as an Olympic sport for the first time.\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9957430568241925, \"rank\": 0.002317517658535885, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia is among the countries sending competitors to the Games' solo breakdance battles.\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 2043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1952, \"end\": 1961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes will windmill, 6-step, and freeze as they improvise moves to hip-hop style beats.\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A new canoe-slalom team event has also been included in the schedule of events.\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kayak cross is described as a combination of all of canoeing's whitewater disciplines and viewers will be able to watch four competitors simultaneously.\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2218, \"end\": 2223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\", \"score\": 0.9976325651531701, \"rank\": 0.002373052895142505, \"text\": \"Kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While it has been 40 years since artistic swimmers first competed at an Olympics, it has been a women-only event until this year's games, at which men will be able to join team events.\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A maximum of two men per team of eight people were able to be picked to compete.\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, as reported byCBC, no men were chosen as part of any of the 18 teams competing in Paris.\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2731, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators will get their first look at Australia's 3x3 women's basketball team at these games.\", \"from\": 2739, \"to\": 2834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2779, \"end\": 2788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the sport was played at the most recent Olympics, this is the first year Australia's women's team, the Gangurrus, has qualified.\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 2970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2915, \"end\": 2924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian Olympic Team could be in for one of its biggest medal hauls yet in Paris, according to a forecast from Neilsen Gracenote, a provider of data and analytics measurements.\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 3155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2972, \"end\": 2986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.95059865984977e-19, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 2976, \"end\": 2999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999964075, \"rank\": 3.605959975437047e-11, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3054, \"end\": 3059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3098, \"end\": 3107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gracenote\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gracenote\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gracenote\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gracenote\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The company's virtual medal table forecast for the 2024 games is based on available results data from key global and continental competitions since the Tokyo 2020 Summer Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 3157, \"to\": 3341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3309, \"end\": 3314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999991314051975, \"rank\": 8.685954581406233e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia comes in fifth up against the other Olympic countries in the table, with 54 medals, a total we only topped in Sydney 2000.\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3343, \"end\": 3352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 3463, \"end\": 3474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.861433633600122e-13, \"text\": \"Sydney 2000\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia won 58 medals that year.\", \"from\": 3477, \"to\": 3511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3477, \"end\": 3486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, as 16 of those were gold, Athens 2004 is seen as Australia's most successful medal haul, given that 17 of the 49 medals won there were gold.\", \"from\": 3513, \"to\": 3662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3548, \"end\": 3559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999102974511, \"rank\": 8.970264549594282e-08, \"text\": \"Athens 2004\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3571, \"end\": 3580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At theTokyo 2020 Olympics, which was held in 2021, due to the onset of the COVID-19 pandemic, Australia took home a total of 46 medals, 17 of those being gold.\", \"from\": 3664, \"to\": 3823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3739, \"end\": 3756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9999999257688642, \"rank\": 7.409938962794216e-08, \"text\": \"COVID-19 pandemic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}, {\"begin\": 3758, \"end\": 3767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Neilsen Gracenote is forecasting Australia will come home from Paris with 15 gold, 23 silver and 16 bronze medals and has noted \\\"achieving this will depend to a great extent on the success of the swimming team.\\\"\", \"from\": 3825, \"to\": 4036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3833, \"end\": 3842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gracenote\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gracenote\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gracenote\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gracenote\"}, {\"begin\": 3858, \"end\": 3867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 3888, \"end\": 3893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is probably not unexpected that Australians competing in swimming, athletics, basketball, cycling, hockey and rowing are allexpected to be medal contendersbut beyond those sports, there are plenty of other events where we are in with a chance.\", \"from\": 4038, \"to\": 4284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shane Rose, a member of the equestrian team, has ridden in three Olympics and has taken home a medal each time.\", \"from\": 4286, \"to\": 4397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4314, \"end\": 4324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.8136230559813168, \"rank\": 0.2290702427687646, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's also the oldest member of the 2024 Australian Olympic team.\", \"from\": 4399, \"to\": 4463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4439, \"end\": 4462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999995084181, \"rank\": 4.91618879669941e-10, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the country's youngest Olympic competitor, 14-year-old Arisa Trew and her fellow skateboarders, including Olympic gold medalist Keegan Palmer, are also likely to be competitive in their events.\", \"from\": 4465, \"to\": 4669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4531, \"end\": 4536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.459123389493908e-25, \"text\": \"Arisa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arisa\"}, {\"begin\": 4604, \"end\": 4617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keegan Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keegan_Palmer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kayaker, Jessica Fox, who earned a gold medal in Tokyo is again part of the canoe-slalom team, but this time her younger sister is along for the ride; Noemie Fox will compete in kayak cross.\", \"from\": 4671, \"to\": 4861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4680, \"end\": 4691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Fox_(actress)\", \"score\": 0.548202986974713, \"rank\": 0.8241415192508661, \"text\": \"Jessica Fox\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Fox_(actress)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Fox_(actress)\"}, {\"begin\": 4720, \"end\": 4725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999991314051975, \"rank\": 8.685954581406233e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4822, \"end\": 4832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noemie_Fox\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noemie Fox\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noemie_Fox\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noemie_Fox\"}, {\"begin\": 4849, \"end\": 4854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\", \"score\": 0.9532446778656106, \"rank\": 0.04904860548423918, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sisters are not the only Australian siblings competing in the canoe-slalom events, as they will be joined by brothers Jean and Pierre van der Westhuyzen.\", \"from\": 4863, \"to\": 5020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4892, \"end\": 4902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9995366421015613, \"rank\": 0.0004635569299922922, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Representing Australia in Paris will also be golfers Minjee and Min Woo competing in golf, brothers and water polo teammates Blake and Lachlan Edwards and sisters Maddison and Teagan Levi, who are rugby sevens players.\", \"from\": 5022, \"to\": 5240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5035, \"end\": 5044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 5048, \"end\": 5053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5147, \"end\": 5152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blake_Carrington\", \"score\": 0.8841515995113487, \"rank\": 0.13102775644837314, \"text\": \"Blake\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blake_Carrington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blake_Carrington\"}, {\"begin\": 5157, \"end\": 5172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lac_Edwards\", \"score\": 0.9999992247602044, \"rank\": 7.752397878075344e-07, \"text\": \"Lachlan Edwards\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lac_Edwards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lac_Edwards\"}, {\"begin\": 5185, \"end\": 5193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angus_Maddison\", \"score\": 0.9933750994940519, \"rank\": 0.006669082514042451, \"text\": \"Maddison\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angus_Maddison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angus_Maddison\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia has selected 460 athletes to compete in the Paris Games, with about half of those making their debut Olympic appearance this year.\", \"from\": 5242, \"to\": 5382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5242, \"end\": 5251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999952442522, \"rank\": 4.221313231728782e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of 32 different sports will be on show and 329 medal events will take place.\", \"from\": 5384, \"to\": 5468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 10,000 athletes representing 206 National Olympic Committees from around the world are taking part.\", \"from\": 5470, \"to\": 5579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5513, \"end\": 5540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9779513817100046, \"rank\": 0.022545720270309294, \"text\": \"National Olympic Committees\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as those countries, a Refugee Olympic Team made up of 37 athletes from 15 countries will compete across 12 sports.\", \"from\": 5581, \"to\": 5703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5611, \"end\": 5631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999996068532573, \"rank\": 3.93146850862172e-07, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A number of Belarusian andRussian athleteswill also compete as Individual Neutral Athletes - without their country's flags, emblems or anthems - due to sanctions against their home nationsover the invasion of Ukraine.\", \"from\": 5705, \"to\": 5922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5717, \"end\": 5727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999458851, \"rank\": 3.343379272082438e-11, \"text\": \"Belarusian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}, {\"begin\": 5914, \"end\": 5921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.8875136945978847, \"rank\": 0.12674279399479632, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Palestinian Olympic Committee, which has eight athletes competing in Paris, had made a last-minute plea for Israel to be banned from the games due to theongoing humanitarian crisis in Gaza.\", \"from\": 5924, \"to\": 6117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5928, \"end\": 5939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.7783424346290058, \"rank\": 0.21697633238269684, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}, {\"begin\": 5997, \"end\": 6002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6036, \"end\": 6042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999817040925587, \"rank\": 1.829622170246571e-05, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the International Olympic Committeehas not upheld the request.\", \"from\": 6119, \"to\": 6190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thefull schedulefor the 2024 Paris Olympicscan be found here.\", \"from\": 6192, \"to\": 6253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6221, \"end\": 6226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be held on Sunday, 11 August in Paris.\", \"from\": 6255, \"to\": 6303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6297, \"end\": 6302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6707070004119545e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But because of the time difference, Australians can watch it earlyon Monday, 12 August.\", \"from\": 6304, \"to\": 6391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It will start a4am AESTfor viewers in Victoria, NSW, Queensland, Tasmania, and the ACT,3am ACSTfor those in the Northern Territory and South Australia, and2am AWSTfor Western Australians.\", \"from\": 6393, \"to\": 6580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6431, \"end\": 6439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_Australian_rules_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9958360549715867, \"rank\": 0.004181125740816315, \"text\": \"Victoria\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_Australian_rules_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_Australian_rules_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6441, \"end\": 6444, \"title\": \"http:/